cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper deals with the problem of generating 3D shapes from 2D views, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The approach involves training a deep generative model, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the disentangled representation of 2D shapes, which is a topic in graphics (cs.GR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the use of generative adversarial networks (GANs) is a popular technique in both machine learning and neural networks (cs.NE).
